benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/priceList - Retrieve priceList for a given subscription and date

covered: Functional success and parameter combinations (TC01-TC04): both parameters, only subscriptionId, only requestedDate, and no-parameter flows are tested for 200 and application/json responses
Input validation and negative parameter cases (TC05, TC07, TC11, TC19): invalid UUID, invalid date format, oversized parameters, and malformed/partial values are tested and expected to return 400/422
Not found / empty data handling (TC06, TC13): non-existent subscription and empty database cases cover 404 or empty/default responses
Authentication negative case (TC08): missing/invalid auth token producing 401 is covered
Dependency and service error handling (TC09, TC20): service unavailable and dependent catalog failure are exercised (503 and 502)
Security vectors (TC10, TC22): SQL injection and XSS attempt scenarios verify rejection and avoiding internal detail leakage
Performance and scalability (TC14, TC15, TC18): normal and peak response time requirements plus large history handling are covered
Resilience and compatibility (TC16, TC17): backward compatibility and retry after transient failures are included
Edge/regression (TC21): date boundary behavior for price list changes is covered
Query robustness (TC12): extra unexpected query parameters are tested to be ignored and not break the response
gaps: Caching behavior and headers not covered: no tests assert Cache-Control, ETag, Last-Modified, or conditional GET (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since) behavior and 304 handling
Rate limiting and throttling absent: no tests simulate bursts or sustained high request rates to verify 429 responses and Retry-After semantics

Response schema and contract validation incomplete: success tests assert a "valid PriceList JSON" but there are no explicit schema/field-level assertions (required fields, types, currency/price formats, nested structures)
Authorization scopes / forbidden scenarios missing: tests cover missing/invalid token (401) but not cases where credentials are valid but lack permission (403)
Header and content negotiation not covered: no tests for varied Accept headers, unsupported media types, or CORS behavior

Standardized error payloads and sensitivity not fully asserted: while error codes are covered, there is no full verification that all error responses follow a consistent schema and never expose internal details
Pagination is not represented: if the endpoint ever returns collections this is missing. Note: endpoint appears to return a single PriceList object so pagination may be not applicable
recommendations: Add explicit contract/schema tests for PriceList responses: assert required fields, data types, numeric/currency formats, enumerations and sample payload snapshots (use JSON Schema or contract tests)
Add caching tests: verify presence and correctness of Cache-Control, ETag, Last-Modified headers; test conditional GETs (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since) and expect 304 when appropriate
Add rate limiting tests: simulate bursts and sustained request rates to validate 429 responses, Retry-After header, and throttle behavior; include client backoff verification
Add authorization scope tests: exercise valid credentials with insufficient privileges to assert 403 forbidden and validate permission checks
Add header and content negotiation tests: vary Accept headers, request unsupported media types and assert correct status (406 or fallback) and ensure Content-Type is consistent
Standardize and test error payload shape: assert schema for error responses (code, message, fields), and test that no stack traces or internal debug data are returned across all error paths
If integration with dependent catalog service is critical, add timeout and slow downstream tests plus circuit-breaker/fallback behavior validation
If endpoint evolves or related endpoints return lists, add pagination tests (limit/offset or token based) and verify large-data correctness; otherwise document why pagination is N/A
Increase granularity of large-data tests: add correctness checks for many adjacent price list changes and stress tests to validate both correctness and performance beyond TC18
Add automated fuzzing and boundary value tests for date boundaries and malformed query values, and include observability checks (correlation IDs, request IDs in logs/responses) if applicable
